properties.headline: Gale Warning issued February 7 at 2:36AM EST until February 8 at 1:00AM EST by NWS Gray ME
properties.description:
* WHAT...North winds 25 to 35 kt with gusts up to 45 kt and seas
5 to 8 feet expected.

* WHERE...Casco and Penobscot Bays.

* WHEN...From 7 AM this morning to 1 AM EST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Winds will increase rapidly in the
afternoon with the strongest gusts from 4 to 8pm
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 7 AM THIS MORNING TO 1 AM EST SATURDAY
